{[show S]
[BID 2!C] [BID 3!H] [BID 4NT] [BID 6!H]
[show NS]
SOUTH expects to bid 2NT at his second turn, but NORTH gives a positive 2\H 
response and his thinking changes! First he supports \Hs, setting the 
trump suit.
 

 
NORTH then bids 3\S, showing first round control. SOUTH tries 4NT (Blackwood) and 
NORTH replies 6\C. This shows a \C void and one Ace, obviously the \SA.
 

 
SOUTH bids 6\H, knowing they must lose the \DA.}


