[Student "S"]
{[show S]
[BID 4NT]
[show NS]
Yes, this has nothing to do with Gerber or Blackwood, but everything to do with smart bidding.
 

 
SOUTH has a 16 points and NORTH has 15, 16 or 17. SOUTH wants to be in 6NT if NORTH has 17, 
but merely a Notrump game if she has 15 or 16.
 

 
The way to find out is to bid 4NT - not Blackwood but merely an invitation to bid 6NT. 
In this case, NORTH has but 15 points and declines the invitation. If her \HQ 
were changed to the \HA she would bid 6NT and collect her twelve easy tricks.}


